    <div class="row">
     <div class="news-wrapper col-6 col-m-12">
      <h1 class="fc-header">
       <img src="/dist/images/icon_news.png"/>
       NEWS
      </h1>
      <p>
       The reset password functionality is currently experiencing issues.  Please contact the FireConnect help desk (979.458.7355) for login assistance.
       <p>
        From 01/01/2019 to 3/10/2019 Fire Departments have reported a cost of $114,624.46 for wildfire suppression in Texas. This cost goes towards the statewide FEMA threshold of $5.7 million that we must meet before anyone in Texas is eligible for FEMA funding after a disaster. This threshold starts over every January 1, so all wildfire reports you enter are greatly appreciated and could help you and your neighbor should disaster strike.
       </p>
      </p>
     </div>
